-----------------------------------------------------------------------
REQUIREMENTS
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
* Perl 5.6.1 or later
* Apache 1.3.x or 2.x with mod_perl
* A DBMS (so far, tested with MySQL only)

* Make sure you have the following Perl Modules installed:

DBI
Class::DBI (0.93)
HTML::Mason
Apache::Session
Apache::DBI
DBIx::DBSchema
DBIx::DataSource
Net::SNMP
NetAddr::IP

----------------------------------------------------------------------
PATCHES
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Netdot needs the following Perl module files patched to fix bugs
and have extra functionality:

YOUR-@INC-PATH/Class/DBI.pm with contrib/ClassDBI.patch
YOUR-@INC-PATH/Apache/Session/Lock/File.pm with contrib/ApacheSession.patch

----------------------------------------------------------------------
SCHEMA CHANGES
----------------------------------------------------------------------

If there are schema changes between your current installation and the 
version you plan to install, it is highly recommended that you:

  * Review README.  If there are changes, it will be documented in 
    this file.
  * Back up your existing database.  mysqldump is one option for MySQL 
    installations.
  * Review contrib/updateschema.data to see what changes will occur.
  * Run updateschema.pl with the appropriate options.

updateschema.pl will manage the schema changes for you.  After you run
this script, you will have to restart httpd.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
INSTALLING THE PACKAGE
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Run these from the main directory and answer any prompts
you encounter:

make install PREFIX=YOUR-PREFIX (i.e: /usr/local/netdot)
make installdb

----------------------------------------------------------------------
APACHE CONFIGURATION
----------------------------------------------------------------------

* Add lines similar to these to your httpd.conf,

<VirtualHost your.ip.address>
    ServerName YOUR-NETDOT-HOSTNAME
    DocumentRoot YOUR-PREFIX/htdocs

    # This line for Apache2+mod_perl2 only
    PerlModule Apache2 Apache::compat

    PerlHandler Apache::DBI
    PerlRequire YOUR-PREFIX/bin/mason.pl

    ##################################################################
    # the following section for Apache 1.3.x only
    ##################################################################
    <Location />
        SetHandler perl-script
        PerlHandler Netdot::Mason
	AuthType Basic
	AuthName "NetDoT"
	AuthUserFile YOUR-PREFIX/htpasswd.users
	require valid-user
    </Location>

    <Location /img>
        SetHandler default-handler	 
    </Location>
    ##################################################################
    # end section
    ##################################################################

    ##################################################################
    # the following section for Apache2 only
    ##################################################################
    <Directory />
        AuthType Basic
        AuthName "UO NetDoT"
        AuthUserFile /etc/httpd/htpasswd.users
        require valid-user
    </Directory>

    <FilesMatch "\.html$">
        SetHandler perl-script
        PerlHandler Netdot::Mason
    </FilesMatch>
    ##################################################################
    # end section
    ##################################################################
</VirtualHost>

* Create the file YOUR-PREFIX/htpasswd.users 
  and add username/passwords to authenticate 
  accesss to the Netdot pages.

* Edit mason.pl to your needs.  
  Pay attention to the Apache2-only directives, and also the paths.
